+      "sourceNotes": "Claim: Three out of four (75%) global knowledge workers use AI at work | Source: VERIFIED (Microsoft & LinkedIn, 2024 Work Trend Index Annual Report, \"AI at Work Is Here. Now Comes the Hard Part,\" May 8, 2024 — headline finding)\nClaim: 78% of AI users bring their own AI tools to work (BYOAI) | Source: VERIFIED (same report — BYOAI is the report's coined term)\nClaim: 31,000 workers surveyed across 31 countries | Source: VERIFIED (same report, methodology — full sample characteristics)\nClaim: DC CAP pilot includes 4-tier data classification, governance pulse questions, sanctioned Claude workspace | Source: GROUNDED (pilot_hub.html; Framework_for_AI_Fluency_v1.5.md; ai_governance/AI_Initiative_Deliverables_Plan.md)\nClaim: Pilot is currently running (launched April 6, 2026; Phase 2 Cards started April 23) | Source: GROUNDED (strategy.md current strategic posture section)\nEditorial: \"Shadow AI\" framing is standard enterprise-security terminology for unsanctioned AI usage. The characterization of BYOAI as the predictable outcome of a governance vacuum is Preston's synthesis of the Microsoft finding applied to DC CAP's pilot context, not a direct quote from the report.\nEditorial: \"Governance gap\" in Try This is Preston's framing, not a Microsoft-report term.\nAdversarial review 20260424: Zero em-dashes. Zero forbidden phrases scanned (leverage/utilize/delve/navigate/landscape/ecosystem/synergy/robust/holistic/stakeholders/foster/enhance/align/transformative/empower/myriad/multifaceted/pivotal/spearhead/showcase/underscore). Zero contrastive \"not X, but Y\" constructions. Zero rhetorical questions. \"Either inside... or inside...\" is a parallel enumeration of two concrete options, not a Preston-forbidden negation. Opens with a concrete fact (75%). Closes with two short declaratives (\"The adoption is already happening. The pilot gives it structure.\") — direct, not TED-talk inflation. Word count main body: 247 words (inside 240–280 band)